cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem related to graph coloring, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The algorithmic aspect of the problem and the analysis of approximation bounds suggest that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the mention of anti-Ramsey numbers and the use of graph theory techniques suggest that it could also belong to cs.GT (Graph Theory).
